'''Rodian Theater''' was a type of theater<ref name="DoR">''[[Dawn of Rebellion]]''</ref> performed in the [[Rodian (language)|Rodian tongue]].<ref name="Obi-Wan & Anakin" /> Rodian Theater troupes often counted [[Drabatan]]s, a [[species]] with pitch-perfect voices who often played the heel, among their number.<ref name="DoR" /> The [[Rodian]] [[Harido Kavila]] created works of Rodian theater that were well-liked by the [[Anomid]] [[Jedi High Council]] member [[Alxa Kress]], and Kress taught [[Jedi Master]] [[Mace Windu]] how to perform Kavila's works in Rodese.<ref name="Obi-Wan & Anakin" />

==Behind the scenes==
Rodian Theater was first mentioned in the current ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[canon]] in ''[[Dawn of Rebellion]]'', a [[2018]] supplement to the ''[[Star Wars Roleplaying]]'' system produced by [[Fantasy Flight Games]].<ref name="DoR" /> The theater was first introduced in the [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] continuity in the [[1996]] [[West End Games]] [[Roleplaying game|roleplaying]] adventure ''[[A Trip to the Country]]'', published in the sourcebook ''[[Shadows of the Empire Planets Guide]]''.<ref name="Trip to the Country">{{WEGCite|story=A Trip to the Country|book=Shadows of the Empire Planets Guide}}</ref>

